etymologies: mid 19th century (in an earlier sense). From eye + bar

definitions: A metal bar with two enlarged ends each containing a hole; specifically a heavy one used to hold a bolt, the end of a cable, or a similar bar, typically in a suspension bridge.
A band of contrasting colour close to an animal's eye, an eyestripe; (in later use) specifically a vertical marking of this kind in a cichlid or other fish.
